<br>
This is a thread I made in the other section when I was doing some testing.<br>
<br>
The blades will also proc with epic pets, so he benefits from both his innate proc and the blade proc damage.  But the proc is level based, so Air pet will get 140 dmg and Epic will get 118 dmg from the weapon procs, narrowing the dmg margin a bit.<br>
<br>
I use the 61 Air pets mostly in PoP groups when I want the defensive mitigation the air pet brings.  Keeping mobs stunned means less damage to tanks, and the air pet stuns a lot more than epic does.  Or in zones where most mobs are casters would also be a good idea.  Try 61 pet with 2 gnoll hide whips, muzzle and burnout 5 then go solo in Sebillis. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
But from a DPS standpoint, in most zones, the Epic still wins due to the proc damage.  And the mana-free, higher DS is nice too.  And it definately holds aggro better than 61 air pet.<br>
