<br>
I believe the damage result I got from my altered parse too.  You can visually tell it's WAY more damage then a pet that just hits for ~60 DPS.  I think the last parse I did cleared 120 because all 3 frogs were hitting the pet and getting burned on the DS while he was chewing on one at a time.  The fight I parsed with epic previous to that was a 1:1 fight and the result was very close to what you saw (90-100 DPS).<br>
<br>
I would say with good confidence the epic pet is around 90+ DPS on any mob it can land procs on and hit decently well.  I agree the 61 air pets are stun machines.  Very good at doing that.  Again, I default to my original statement that choosing what pet to use is situational.<br>
<br>
About the 61 air pet in Sebilis with Gnoll hide Lariats, burnout V... That means you are level 62 at least, and at that level, Sebilis is NOT worth doing anymore unless you go deep in.  Nearly the whole first floor turns light blue to you at 61.  At 62 it's much worse.  So even though, sure I could have a nice pet at level 62 for farming Sebilis, but I don't get crap for exp.<br>
<br>
That much being said, do the same thing with epic.  Give him Gnoll hide lariats, Burnout 4, etc.  He will be a machine too, but you still get exp like crazy. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
